column2: Field is used when importing via MusicBrainz (since Mp3tag v3.13).
Field is used when importing via Discogs and MusicBrainz (since Mp3tag v3.13).
Field that is used by iTunes to mark albums as compilation. Either enter the value 1 or delete the field.
Field that is used by iTunes to mark tracks as podcasts. Either enter the value 1 or delete the field.
This description is for only ID3v2 tags. The playcounter is an optional value. The Rating is an integer between 1 (worst) and 255 (best). Syntax: Email|Rating|Playcounter

Abstraction on POPULARIMETER as used in MediaMonkey. Track rating from 1 = Bad to 5 = Very good. You can also enter stars * (and - for half stars) for rating the track. Use Options → Tags → Advanced to always display POPULARIMETER values.

Abstraction on POPULARIMETER as used in Windows Media Player. Track rating from 1 = Bad to 5 = Very good. You can also enter stars * for rating the track. Use Options → Tags → Advanced to always display POPULARIMETER values.
Syntax: xxx||Lyrics where xxx = Language of the lyrics
column3: abbreviated by 3 characters according to ISO-639-2.
